HEADWORD: Adarce
<hw>A*dar"ce</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adarce</ets>, <ets>adarca</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>A saltish
concretion on reeds and grass in marshy grounds in Galatia. It is soft
and porous, and was formerly used for cleansing the skin from freckles
and tetters, and also in leprosy.</def> <rj><au>Dana.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

